trans-unit.source:
To use MagicAI, first download the models as instructed. Once you're set up, you can just request anything into the **prompt** field and press **Generate**.
Please note that the first generation after opening up Magic will always take a bit longer to prepare.
trans-unit.target:
To use MagicAI, first download the models as instructed. Once you're set up, you can just request anything into the **prompt** field and press **Generate**.
Please note that the first generation after opening up Magic will always take a bit longer to prepare.

trans-unit.source: MagicAI uses **Stable Diffusion**, a text-to-image deep learning model that can run and generate small images on most powerful computers in a matter of seconds.
trans-unit.target: MagicAI uses **Stable Diffusion**, a text-to-image deep learning model that can run and generate small images on most powerful computers in a matter of seconds.

trans-unit.source: MagicAI uses [Stable Diffusion v2](https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-2-base), optimized for CoreML on Apple Silicon Macs only.
trans-unit.target: MagicAI uses [Stable Diffusion v2](https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-2-base), optimized for CoreML on Apple Silicon Macs only.

trans-unit.source: At the moment, it is not possible to use a different AI model with MagicAI.
trans-unit.target: At the moment, it is not possible to use a different AI model with MagicAI.

trans-unit.source: Because of the complexity of the AI model, MagicAI needs to ensure a good performance on all systems. Stable Diffusion has already been optimized for CoreML, Apple's machine learning platform, but exclusively for Apple Silicon chips, which all provide the required efficiency for running the AI model.
trans-unit.target: Because of the complexity of the AI model, MagicAI needs to ensure a good performance on all systems. Stable Diffusion has already been optimized for CoreML, Apple's machine learning platform, but exclusively for Apple Silicon chips, which all provide the required efficiency for running the AI model.

trans-unit.source:
In many ways! For example, you can use it as a *magical* drawing reference generator. Or maybe as a helpful assistant in your workflow, to improve your current work: you could draw a stub of a landscape and ask MagicAI to remake it photorealisticly, in the style of an specific artist or in any other way you want.
You could even ask it to generate an object and then copy it with the background removed by right-clicking the layer and selecting **Quick Look**.
trans-unit.target:
In many ways! For example, you can use it as a *magical* drawing reference generator. Or maybe as a helpful assistant in your workflow, to improve your current work: you could draw a stub of a landscape and ask MagicAI to remake it photorealisticly, in the style of an specific artist or in any other way you want.
You could even ask it to generate an object and then copy it with the background removed by right-clicking the layer and selecting **Quick Look**.

trans-unit.source: MagicAI supports adding a base image to your generation in a process known as **inpainting**. To do so, just select **Use drawing as reference** from the MagicAI panel. You can use your own drawing to guide the model into creating an image suited for you. Be thoughtful of your prompt though, since it needs to be sufficiently aligned with the contents of your drawing for the magic to work.
trans-unit.target: MagicAI supports adding a base image to your generation in a process known as **inpainting**. To do so, just select **Use drawing as reference** from the MagicAI panel. You can use your own drawing to guide the model into creating an image suited for you. Be thoughtful of your prompt though, since it needs to be sufficiently aligned with the contents of your drawing for the magic to work.

trans-unit.source: You can use MagicAI up to 15 times for free per month, or up to 30 times per month with an active Magic+ subscription. Magic Unlimited grants you unlimited generations.
trans-unit.target: You can use MagicAI up to 15 times for free per month, or up to 30 times per month with an active Magic+ subscription. Magic Unlimited grants you unlimited generations.

trans-unit.source:
**Strength**: when using a drawing as a reference, this value determines the influence of the original drawing in the final result.
**Steps**: the amount of times the image refines through the model pipeline. The more steps, the better the image will be. Please mind the number of actual steps may be automatically adjusted by the system.
**Seed**: the random, unique generator for the initial noise that will be polished into the final generated image. A pairing of the same seed, amount of steps and prompt will yield the same result.
trans-unit.target:
**Strength**: when using a drawing as a reference, this value determines the influence of the original drawing in the final result.
**Steps**: the amount of times the image refines through the model pipeline. The more steps, the better the image will be. Please mind the number of actual steps may be automatically adjusted by the system.
**Seed**: the random, unique generator for the initial noise that will be polished into the final generated image. A pairing of the same seed, amount of steps and prompt will yield the same result.

trans-unit.source: To save your generated images, simply press the **Save image** button in the MagicAI panel once your generation is done. If you choose to discard it instead, your monthly rate will not be affected.
trans-unit.target: To save your generated images, simply press the **Save image** button in the MagicAI panel once your generation is done. If you choose to discard it instead, your monthly rate will not be affected.
